Tesla Inc. is asking its shareholders to vote today on two questions:=09Sho=
uld Elon Musk get back the gigantic pile of options that Tesla granted him =
in 2018, and that a Delaware judge clawed back earlier this year?=09Should =
Tesla move its state of incorporation from Delaware to Texas, so no Delawar=
e judge can ever do this again?The shareholder meeting starts at 4:30 p.m. =
New York time, but basically everyone votes electronically before the meeti=
ng, and as of this morning it appeared to be over:Tesla Inc. shares jumped =
in early trading after Elon Musk said shareholders voted =E2=80=9Cby wide m=
argins=E2=80=9D in favor of re-approving his compensation package and movin=
g the company=E2=80=99s state of incorporation to Texas.The chief executive=
 officer posted about the voting results on X, the social media site he own=
s, hours before Tesla=E2=80=99s annual meeting Thursday in Austin, sharing =
two charts suggesting the proposals had been approved. Tesla shares jumped =
as much as 7.2% before the start of regular trading.Here=E2=80=99s Musk=E2=
=80=99s tweet (sorry, X post), saying that =E2=80=9CBoth Tesla shareholder =
resolutions are currently passing by wide margins,=E2=80=9D with little Exc=
el graphs showing almost 1.4 billion shares voted for Musk=E2=80=99s pay an=
d more than 2 billion shares voted for the move to Texas.
  [1]
