argo had =E2=80=9Cstrict quotas regulating the number of daily =E2=80=98sol=
utions=E2=80=99=C2=A0that its bankers must reach,=E2=80=9D and its managers=
 would =E2=80=9Cconstantly hound, berate, demean and threaten employees to =
meet these unreachable quotas.=E2=80=9DAnd so the employees, rather than wo=
rking with each customer to build a suite of products that met the customer=
=E2=80=99s needs and deepened her relationship with the bank, would just go=
