ikely to give the hedge fund nonrecourse financing on this trade. Also, as =
I said in a footnote, the financing bank is presumably marking the position=
 to market and calling for margin if the underlying loans deteriorate, mean=
ing that in practice it will not bear any loss unless things go really wron=
g.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So my schematic version overstates the r=
isk to the banking system of this financing: Even if the SRT goes bad, the =
financing bank is unlikely to lose much money. But it=E2=80=99s not impossi=
ble, and in particular, it=E2=80=99s a worrying sort of=C2=A0<em>systemic=
=C2=A0</em>risk. If all the SRTs go bad at once, hedge funds that do a lot =
of SRT trades really might not be able to pay back their repo lenders, and =
at exactly the worst time.</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=
