w of them will be good at chess. But to attract more, it might help to have=
 a strong grandmaster lying around. The grandmaster doesn=E2=80=99t necessa=
rily have to do much trading or coding or whatever; you can just trot her o=
ut as a recruiting prop. =E2=80=9COh that firm has great chess players, it =
must be a good place for me to work=E2=80=9D is a thought process that will=
 occur in some of the employees you want, and the cost of employing a <a hr=
ef=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35707099.259299/aHR0cHM=
6Ly93d3cubGlua2VkaW4uY29tL3B1bHNlL2hvdy1tdWNoLWRvZXMtY2hlc3MtZ3JhbmRtYXN0ZX=
